        <p class="p-line-height3" >The Jamaican Association for Debating and Empowerment (JADE), founded in 2013 by UTech Jamaica alumnus Germaine Barrett, is a prominent organization in Jamaica dedicated to promoting debate, public speaking, and empowerment initiatives. JADE provides numerous programs and services, including workshops on effective communication, conflict management, and critical thinking skills. Through various initiatives, JADE supports the growth of debate clubs in schools and offers training to foster a culture of respectful discourse.</p>

        <p class="p-line-height3">Guided by its mission to foster empowerment through debating, public speaking and critical thinking in Jamaica, The Jamaican Association for Debating and Empowerment (JADE) Limited has achieved significant success and continues to provide invaluable expertise to in communications skills development through these four main dimensions: - Debating, Public Speaking and Critical Thinking Training - Debate Adjudication Services - Planning and Administration of Debate and Public Speaking Competitions - Citizen Empowerment and Conflict Resolution</p>

        <p class="p-line-height3">JADE is particularly active in organizing competitions and partnering with organizations to facilitate debates, like the Burger King National Secondary Schools Debating Competition and collaborations with the Jamaica Debates Commission (JDC). The JDC partnership, initiated in 2019, supports JADE's role in enriching Jamaica's debating culture, focusing on youth and civil discourse around national issues. </p>

